      "content": "It is fundamentally an environmental necessity, not just a traffic management trick. By putting a price on driving in dense areas, congestion pricing directly discourages the use of single-occupancy gasoline vehicles, which is the primary driver of urban emissions. This mechanism forces behavioral change toward cleaner alternatives like public transit or electric vehicles, making it a critical piece of climate action infrastructure.",
      "source": "target",
