    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. But what about the people who live in the outer boroughs or further out and don't have great transit options? Seems like they'd get hit pretty hard by the costs while the people in the center don't really notice. Doesn't that make it a bit of a regressive policy?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
